My rule is that a simple conditional without braces can go on one line:<p><pre><code>    if (not_true) return;
</code></pre>
Anything longer goes on the next line, within brances.

Thank you! I'm really glad it connected. I love this from Goethe:<p><pre><code>  Then indecision brings its own delays, 
          And days are lost lamenting over lost days. 
          Are you in earnest? Seize this very minute; 
          What you can do, or dream you can do, begin it; 
          Boldness has genius, power and magic in it.</code></pre>
